    {
      "id": "RQ-0022",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Serialize managed-session rotation across overlapping tool calls",
      "description": "Principles violated: E) Make bugs hard to write, F) Fail fast, G) Least astonishment, J) Consistency/Integrity.\n\nWhy it matters: overlapping implicit-session calls race on shared mutable state, so a later fresh launch can be silently discarded by an older call finishing later, and a managed-session replacement can close a browser that another in-flight tool call is still using. Under load this sends follow-up auto calls to the wrong browser or fails active work mid-command.\n\nMinimal proposed fix: introduce per-managed-session serialization or generation checks around state transitions and replacement cleanup so only the latest relevant completion can promote or close the managed session. Treat stale completions as non-authoritative for managed-session mutation.\n\nAcceptance criteria: add concurrency-focused regressions covering both stale-completion rollback and mid-flight close hazards; confirm later `sessionMode: \"fresh\"` launches remain authoritative; confirm overlapping auto calls do not have their session closed out from under them; verify `npm run verify` stays green.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "maintenance",
        "concurrency",
        "sessions",
        "correctness"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "extensions/agent-browser/index.ts",
        "extensions/agent-browser/lib/runtime.ts",
        "test/agent-browser.resume-state.test.ts",
        "npx tsx"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "path: extensions/agent-browser/index.ts:882-887 :: managed-session activity, name, cwd, and fresh ordinal live in mutable module-scoped variables shared by every tool call.",
        "path: extensions/agent-browser/index.ts:949-962 :: each execution plans its managed-session transition against the current shared state before any async subprocess work completes.",
        "path: extensions/agent-browser/index.ts:1238-1259 :: completion mutates shared managed-session state and may immediately `closeManagedSession(...)` for the previously active session.",
        "path: extensions/agent-browser/lib/runtime.ts:348-369 :: `resolveManagedSessionState(...)` always treats the completing call's `managedSessionName` as authoritative when it succeeds, regardless of whether a newer call already promoted a different session.",
        "repro: `npx tsx <<'EOF' ... start auto open https://example.com/slow-base, wait 5ms, start --profile Default open https://example.com/fast-fresh with sessionMode:'fresh', then run snapshot -i ... EOF` :: expected the follow-up implicit snapshot to stay on the fresh session :: actual `details.sessionName` reverted to the base session and the invocation log included an unexpected `--session <fresh> close`.",
        "repro: `npx tsx <<'EOF' ... establish implicit session, start snapshot -i, wait 25ms, start fresh profiled open ... EOF` :: expected the in-flight snapshot to complete against the original managed session :: actual snapshot returned `session was closed mid-command` after the fresh launch triggered `--session <base> close` before the snapshot completed."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Add a managed-session mutation guard such as a per-call generation token or serialized critical section around rotation and replacement cleanup.",
        "Ensure replacement `close` only happens after no in-flight tool call still depends on the outgoing managed session, or suppress close for stale completions.",
        "Add regression coverage for both overlapping rotation outcomes and stale completion ordering.",
        "Verify by running `npm run verify` plus the two concurrency repro scripts and confirming follow-up auto calls stay on the newest session while overlapping in-flight calls still succeed."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "scan: Cancellation, overlapping tool calls, rapid sequential agent_browser invocations, and temp-root lifecycle under load.",
